# Modal central template

When adding or editing a **sheet, popover, or any structured window** that has a title row + body (Guardian HQ style):

- **Must** use ``Modal`` from ``Sources/GuardianHQ/General/Utilities/Templates/Modal.swift`` — do not hand-roll a `VStack` title strip + ad-hoc `Divider` / borders for the same chrome.
- **Must not** add a second rule line under the header inside ``bodyContent``; ``Modal`` already draws exactly one ``GuardianModalHeaderSeparator`` (1pt ``theme.borderSubtle``). Extra `Divider`s there cause inconsistent headers across the app.
- Use ``GuardianModalLayout`` for the only supported header/body padding constants; do not duplicate those numbers on individual screens.
- Prefer shared action buttons (e.g. ``GuardianPrimaryProminentButton``, ``GuardianThemedButton``) in ``headerActions`` so modal actions match the rest of the theme.
- Reference implementation and live preview: **Theme** panel → sections **Typography** (above) then **Modal shell**.
